metadata.name: Wondering #175
metadata.description:
The work contains a fluid simulation. I put random forces into the simulation and let it run 500 steps to create a flow field and then use it to generate the visuals. 

I choose fluid simulation instead of curl noise or any other noise function because I believe the fluid simulation could generate a movement that's more dynamic and organic. The result is a combination of big and small vortices.


This piece requires WebGL2 to run, please check and make sure this runs on your device in advance. Also you can press the spacebar to toggle the camera control.

metadata.name: Moonlight Impression #58
metadata.description:
I always love to feel the moonlight falling on the mountains and flowing clouds. There is always a scenery in deep inside, it is the kind of picture that you might think of when you are  alone in the deep night. In my case, that's somewhere there's a yellow moon.

This piece presents the combination of the yellow moon with different elements such as mountains, forests and clouds in some transformations.

Many dots of different sizes and colors are used to paint the picture, trying to replicate the texture of a glue painting.

Made with p5js.


Variables:
- 27 sky color schemas
- 27 mountain color schemas

Control(in live view):
- Press [s] to save a high-res png image

metadata.name: Itaya #29
metadata.description: 'Itaya' means belonging to or resident of a place, almost like a co-ordinate system that always orients us to the canvas. This work plays with this notion of fixed positioning of loops and grids, by adding minor displacements to the rendered position of the unicode characters as a study in nature of things and their organic arrangements.

metadata.name: Efflorescence #19
metadata.description:
Efflorescence is a piece that bridges between Pouya and Fatima's hand crafted tiles and Gorilla Sun's generative work, and reflects their collective love for patterns and colour. Efflorescence is a generative token that creates unique compositions by random arrangement of different tiles and the colorisation thereof.

This generative token would not have been possible without Zeno Zeng's SVG runtime for P5JS!

Press the down arrow button to export an SVG of the artwork. In live view stroke width can be adjusted by zooming in and out.

metadata.name: Sketching #10
metadata.description:
Rules : 
  1. Start with either a line or a circle from a number of random points in the space.
  2. A line can only spawn a circle at the end. 
  3. A circle can spawn both lines and circles before it completes the full circle.
  4. A circle can sometimes spawn an inner circle.
  5. Smaller elements will spawn randomly along with the lines.

This was inspired by the patterns in Marvel's movie : Eternals. I enjoyed the line growing animation with basic geometry ( line and circle ). Combining this with the rules It generates interesting results.

To add more variety to the rendering, I've added the dash lines in instead of only solid lines. Also the 'lines' consist of thousands of small dots to give it randomness and a bit of texture feeling.

metadata.name: Stippled Impressions #62
metadata.description:
The grainy texture of stippling has always appealed to me. Charcoal and graphite drawings on rough paper have a similar aesthetic I find appealing. There is something in the rough texture that feels dreamlike.

This project includes the following features: line count, rendering method, interpolation method, line shape, and color palette.

P5.js

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #100
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."
